  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with recurrence of symptomatic persistent atrial fibrillation after at least
             one ablation procedure,

          -  with the last ablation procedure at least 3 months ago.

          -  at least one unsuccessful attempt of antiarrhythmic drug

          -  oral anticoagulation for at least 4 weeks prior to ablation

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  LA thrombus
      </textblock>
